Represents an external session created outside Okta, typically by third-party 
applications or identity providers that are integrated with Okta.  The externalsessionid is often used in the context of SSO integrations with third-party applications (like Salesforce, Google Apps, etc.) or federated identity systems. It links an external session to the user's Okta session when the user is accessing applications that are integrated with Okta.

Represents the primary session that a user is associated with when they log into 
Okta. This ID is generated when a user successfully authenticates and creates 
a session within Okta.  A user can have a single rootsessionid per login, but this ID may persist across multiple applications if the user is authenticated via Single Sign-On (SSO) or other integrated Okta features.
